  "chapter": {
    "number": 5,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "A Lamentation against Israel"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          "Hear this word, O house of Israel, this lamentation I take up against you:"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "“Fallen is Virgin Israel,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "never to rise again.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "She lies abandoned on her land,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "with no one to raise her up.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          "This is what the Lord GOD says:",
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "“The city that marches out a thousand strong",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "will only see a hundred return,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and the one that marches out a hundred strong",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "will have but ten left in the house of Israel.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "A Call to Repentance"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          "For this is what the LORD says to the house of Israel:",
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "“Seek Me and live!",
            "poem": 1
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Do not seek Bethel or go to Gilgal;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "do not journey to Beersheba,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "for Gilgal will surely go into exile,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and Bethel will come to nothing.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 1310
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Seek the LORD and live,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "or He will sweep like fire through the house of Joseph;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "it will devour everything,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "with no one at Bethel to extinguish it.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "There are those who turn justice into wormwood",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and cast righteousness to the ground.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He who made the Pleiades and Orion,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "who turns darkness into dawn",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and darkens day into night,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "who summons the waters of the sea",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and pours them over the face of the earth—",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "the LORD is His name—",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He flashes destruction on the strong,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "so that fury comes upon the stronghold.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "There are those who hate the one who reproves in the gate",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and despise him who speaks with integrity.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Therefore, because you trample on the poor",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and exact from him a tax of grain,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "you will never live",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "in the stone houses you have built;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "you will never drink the wine",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "from the lush vineyards you have planted.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For I know that your transgressions are many",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and your sins are numerous.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "You oppress the righteous by taking bribes;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "you deprive the poor of justice in the gate.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Therefore, the prudent keep silent in such times,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "for the days are evil.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Seek good, not evil,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "so that you may live.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "And the LORD, the God of Hosts,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "will be with you, as you have claimed.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Hate evil and love good;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "establish justice in the gate.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Perhaps the LORD, the God of Hosts,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "will be gracious to the remnant of Joseph.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Woe to Rebellious Israel"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 16,
        "content": [
          "Therefore this is what the LORD, the God of Hosts, the Lord, says:",
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "“There will be wailing in all the public squares",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and cries of ‘Alas! Alas!’ in all the streets.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "The farmer will be summoned to mourn,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the mourners to wail.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 17,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "There will be wailing in all the vineyards,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "for I will pass through your midst,”",
            "poem": 2
          },
          "says the LORD."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 18,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Woe to you who long for the Day of the LORD!",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "What will the Day of the LORD be for you?",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "It will be darkness and not light.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 19,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "It will be like a man who flees from a lion,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "only to encounter a bear,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "or who enters his house and rests his hand against the wall,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "only to be bitten by a snake.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 20,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Will not the Day of the LORD",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "be darkness and not light,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "even gloom with no brightness in it?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 21,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "“I hate, I despise your feasts!",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I cannot stand the stench of your solemn assemblies.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 22,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Even though you offer Me burnt offerings and grain offerings,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I will not accept them;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "for your peace offerings of fattened cattle",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I will have no regard.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 23,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Take away from Me the noise of your songs!",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I will not listen to the music of your harps.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 24,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "But let justice roll on like a river,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and righteousness like an ever-flowing stream.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 25,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Did you bring Me sacrifices and offerings",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "forty years in the wilderness, O house of Israel?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 26,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "You have taken along Sakkuth your king",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and Kaiwan your star god,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 1311
          },
          {
            "text": "the idols you made for yourselves.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 27,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Therefore I will send you into exile beyond Damascus,”",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 1312
          },
          {
            "text": "says the LORD, whose name is the God of Hosts.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
